-- INTERVIEW-Mediolanum CEO says could buy around half of stake Fininvest must sell
-- 
-- Fri Oct 10, 2014 05:20AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, Oct 10 (Reuters) - Mediolanum <MED.MI> Chief Executive Ennio Doris said he is interested in buying up to half of the 20 percent stake in the asset manager that holding company Fininvest must sell, Doris told Reuters.

The Bank of Italy has told Fininvest, controlled by the family of former Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi, that it must cut its stake in Mediolanum to 9.9 percent from around 30 percent at present. [ID:nL6N0S50BG] "I am certainly interested in buying not all the shares (sold by Fininvest) but a stake not exceeding 10 percent," Doris, whose family owns around 40 percent of Mediolanum, told reuters in a telephone interview. He said that also members of the Berlusconi family could be interested in buying Mediolanum shares from Fininvest.